---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base title="Affiliate Disclosure | LearnEnglish.Life" description="Learn how LearnEnglish.Life earns money through affiliate partnerships and how this affects our reviews.">
 <Header />
 
 <!-- Hero -->
 <section class="bg-emerald-700 py-12">
 <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
 <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Affiliate Disclosure
 </h1>
 <p class="text-emerald-100 text-lg">Last updated: April 5, 2026
 </p>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Main Content -->
 <section class="py-12 bg-slate-900/60">
 <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
 <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none">
 
 <div class="bg-emerald-900/30 border border-emerald-700 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
 <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-emerald-200 mb-2">In Short</h2>
 <p class="text-emerald-200">LearnEnglish.Life earns money when you click our links and make a purchase or sign up. <strong class="text-emerald-200">This does not affect our reviews.</strong> We only recommend platforms we genuinely believe are valuable for English learners.
 </p>
 </div>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">1. What Are Affiliate Links?</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">Affiliate links are special URLs that track when you click them and make a purchase or sign up for a service. When this happens, we may receive a commission at <strong class="text-neutral-200">no extra cost to you</strong>.
 </p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6">For example, if you sign up for iTalki through our link and purchase credits, iTalki may pay us a percentage of that sale. This helps us keep LearnEnglish.Life running.
 </p>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">2. How Affiliate Links Work on Our Site</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">You can identify affiliate links on LearnEnglish.Life by:
 </p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-neutral-300 mb-6 space-y-2">
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Links in reviews:</strong> Buttons like "Try Free Trial" or "Sign Up" that lead to platform registration pages</li>
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Comparison tables:</strong> Links to pricing or signup pages of compared platforms</li>
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Recommendation sections:</strong> Links to recommended tools or services</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6">We use URL parameters (like <code class="text-emerald-300">?ref=learnenglish</code> or UTM codes) to track which links you click, but these don't affect your experience or pricing.
 </p>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">3. Our Affiliate Relationships</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">We participate in affiliate programs with various English learning platforms. Some of the platforms we may earn commissions from include:
 </p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-neutral-300 mb-6 space-y-2">
 <li>iTalki</li>
 <li>Preply</li>
 <li>Cambly</li>
 <li>Verbling</li>
 <li>iTalki alternatives and similar platforms</li>
 <li>Online course providers (Udemy, Coursera, etc.)</li>
 <li>Language learning apps</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6">This is not an exhaustive list. We may earn commissions from any linked platform.
 </p>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">4. How This Affects Our Reviews</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">
 <strong class="text-neutral-200">Our reviews are not influenced by affiliate relationships.</strong> Here's our promise:
 </p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-neutral-300 mb-6 space-y-2">
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Independent research:</strong> We research and write reviews based on platform features, pricing, user feedback, and our own analysis, not what earns us money</li>
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Honest ratings:</strong> We give honest ratings even if a platform doesn't have an affiliate program</li>
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">No pay-to-play:</strong> We don't accept payment for positive reviews. A platform cannot pay to be recommended</li>
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Regular updates:</strong> We update reviews when platforms change their services, regardless of affiliate impact</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6">We believe our credibility is our most valuable asset. Misleading readers would destroy trust and ultimately hurt our business more than any short-term affiliate gain.
 </p>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">5. Why We Use Affiliate Links</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">LearnEnglish.Life is an independent review and resource site with minimal overhead. However, we still have costs:
 </p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-neutral-300 mb-6 space-y-2">
 <li>Server and hosting costs</li>
 <li>Domain registration</li>
 <li>Content creation and research</li>
 <li>Site maintenance and development</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6">Affiliate commissions help cover these costs while keeping the site free for users. We don't charge for access, subscriptions, or premium content.
 </p>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">6. Your Cost</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6">
 <strong class="text-neutral-200">Using our links costs you nothing extra.</strong> In most cases, the prices are identical whether you use our link or go directly to the platform. In some cases, platforms may offer exclusive deals or bonuses for users who come through our links, but this is disclosed when it happens.
 </p>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">7. Sponsored Content</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">Occasionally, a platform may pay us to:
 </p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-neutral-300 mb-6 space-y-2">
 <li>Create a sponsored review or article</li>
 <li>Feature them prominently on our site</li>
 <li>Include them in a "sponsored" comparison</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">When this happens, we:
 </p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-neutral-300 mb-6 space-y-2">
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Always disclose</strong> that content is sponsored at the top of the article</li>
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Maintain editorial control:</strong> sponsors cannot change our opinions or ratings</li>
 <li><strong class="text-neutral-200">Mark clearly:</strong> sponsored content looks different and is labeled</li>
 </ul>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">8. FTC Compliance</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">LearnEnglish.Life complies with the Federal Trade Commission's guidelines regarding endorsements and testimonials. This means:
 </p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-neutral-300 mb-6 space-y-2">
 <li>We disclose material connections (affiliate relationships)</li>
 <li>Our reviews reflect honest opinions</li>
 <li>We don't make claims about products we haven't actually evaluated</li>
 </ul>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-200 mt-8 mb-4">9. Questions?</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6">If you have questions about our affiliate relationships or how they affect our content, we're happy to clarify:<br>
 <strong class="text-neutral-200">Email:</strong> affiliates@learnenglish.life
 </p>

 <div class="bg-amber-900/40 rounded-xl p-6 mt-8 border border-amber-300">
 <h3 class="font-bold text-amber-200 mb-2">Transparency Notice</h3>
 <p class="text-sm text-amber-200">This disclosure was created by our editorial team to ensure transparency with our users.
 </p>
 </div>

 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <Footer />
</Base>
